### Command for training tokenizer for creole MT models.
### I am assuming that you have installed YANMTT
### Language codes are in creoles_list.txt. For example mfe stands for mauritian creole.

cd <PATH TO YANMTT FOLDER>

bash create_autotokenizer.sh <tokenizer size> <PATH TO TOKENIZER> albert . <number of training sentences to consider> 1&

## Example of how the tokenizer for models reported in the paper was trained.
## Note 1: The training files should end in the 3 character language codes which will be specified during training.
## Note 2: You may train a special tokenizer just for a single language pair. We just trained one in case we wanted to do multilingual training.
## Note 3: "albert" implies that a sentencepeice model will be trained. Use mbart for BPE.
## Note 4: Use the albert prefix for tokenizer name so as to avoid headaches. For example, albert-creoles64k.

